name: polyline creatures i
description:
A set of creatures generated with polylines, custom code that draws lines using many others. Plus some recursiveness. Plus some randomness. Plus some intention from the artist to create partially organic lifeless lifeforms.

Part of the exploration of what can be done with simple lines, inspired by the works of Eusebio Sempere in the 1960s.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro.

Made with Processing, 3000x3000px png.
